author: Suhas Nayse
title: Rasika, Vaishnavi crash out of All India Senior Ranking tournament
text:
NAGPUR: City's challenge in the All India Senior Ranking Badminton tournament came to an end with the loss of Rasika Raje and Vaishnavi Bhale at Kakinada on Friday. 

Seventh seed Rasika lost 12-21, 6-21 against top seed Ruthvika Shivani in the quarterfinal. Earlier in the morning, Rasika had dismissed Ira Sharma 21-10, 21-6 in the second round. 

Pune's experienced shuttler Mudra Dhainje defeated Vaishnavi 21-16, 21-18 in the women's singles second round. 

In the mixed doubles second round, fourth seeds Utkarsh Arora and Mohita Sahdev beat Nagpur's Govind Sahasrabuddhe and Vaishnavi Bhale 21-10, 21-18.
